result.execSummary:
The defendant Francisco Hernandez Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(2nd w/in3 Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Sheriff's Department for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.

records.addlTxt: Documents verified with scanning; Paper file destroyed, retained electronically (scanned).

Def appeared in person.  Atty Mark D. Bensen for State.  Interpreter appearing in person: Vicki Bermudez;   Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found.  Defendant does not wish to obtain counsel; Colloquy re: waiver of atty; Defendant waives right to counsel, Court accepts waiver; Agreement reached;  Guilty plea entered. Court finds def guilty on Ct. 1, enters judgment of conviction; Court imposes a fine of $516 (includes DNA surcharge) to be paid by 10/2/15 or judgment shall be entered for nonpayment.  Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Sheriff's Department for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Court informs Defendant of DNA expungement rights.

Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found.  Court orders $100.00 signature bond.  Hearing scheduled for September 25, 2015 at 11:00 am.
